URL reference: https://coralogix.com/blog/building-visibility-and-resilience-across-kubernetes/
DateReviewed: 2026-01-03
Description: Today's article is about visibility and resilience with Kubernetes through monitoring and logging. We start with background on why security and monitoring matter in Kubernetes, and explains how it makes things quicker but that means a bit more complexity on the security side. As we dive deeper, we first look at shared responsibility, which means if you use a cloud provider or a managed service, some of the security is provided by the supplier and some is done by you, and it's important to know which is what. They then pivot to self-managed K8s - the most control, but the most responsibility. They have six strong best practices, and they are all good. They also advise centralizing and aggregating logs, which is also good. Next they look at managed K8s, and they explain who is responsible for what. There are still lots of things on the customer side, but less items means more time for focus. They talk a bit more about what telemetry you want, and how to monitor this. They go through some example threat scenarios along with some real-world use cases, and pitch centralizing observability. I'll tip my cap as they have exactly ONE para for a product pitch.
BottomLine: Good article on Monitoring strategies for Kubernetes
