URL reference: https://hwchiu.medium.com/why-and-why-not-of-enabling-swap-in-kubernetes-08c094a8d427
DateReviewed: 2026-01-07
Description: Interesting topic of swap, and how Kubernetes up until now has mostly avoided using it. We start with a quick primer on swap, which is just using disk space to free up RAM for something else temporarily. They then explain why K8s avoids swap - mostly for performance and quality of service reasons, because swap brings in an unknown variable when allocating or using memory. The issue is that without swap, you are limited to physical memory, and subject to dreaded OOM (out of memory) errors. With better management and newer practices, there is a revisit going on to thing about enabling swap in K8s in certain cases. So, something to consider - it's a good topic and article.
BottomLine: Why to use or not use swap on Kubernetes
